Objective: To demonstrate the lifecycle of containers for efficient management and optimization of Docker container orchestration

Step 1: Demonstrate Docker container lifecycle management
    1.1 Pull a Docker image from Docker hub using the following 
      command: sudo docker pull nginx

    1.2 Execute the following command to run a container from the Nginx image: 
      sudo docker run -d --name my-nginx -p 8080:80 nginx
    1.3 Run the following command to list the running containers:
      sudo docker ps
    1.4 Open a web browser and navigate to http://localhost:8080 to view the default Nginx welcome page
    1.5 Execute the following command to inspect the details of the running container, including its configuration and                  networking information. 
        sudo docker inspect my-nginx
